(WORKING PAPER ON SPECTRUM COMPATIBILITY ANALYSIS) Tj T*
(Draft Revision 1 -- For Comment) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Introduction) Tj T*
(10  This working paper presents a spectrum compatibility analysis for proposed new radio) Tj T*
(14  services operating in the 3.5-3.7 GHz band. The analysis evaluates potential) Tj T*
(18  interference between new entrants and incumbent FSS earth stations.) Tj T*
(22  1.2 The executive summary provides an overview of compatibility findings.) Tj T*
(25  Based on the analysis, limited spectrum sharing is feasible under the defined) Tj T*
(26  protection criteria, subject to operational constraints described in Section 6.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(2. Background and Scope) Tj T*
(30  2.1 The 3.5 GHz band has been identified as a candidate for new broadband services.) Tj T*
(34  2.4 Terminology: the term 'incumbent' refers to services with prior coordination) Tj T*
(36  rights. Capitalization follows ITU style guide conventions.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3. Interference Analysis Methodology) Tj T*
(40  3.1 The propagation model is detailed in Section 5.1.) Tj T*
(44  3.2 The compatibility analysis evaluates single-entry interference from a) Tj T*
(48  representative transmitter. The protection criterion adopted is I/N = -6 dB.) Tj T*
(52  3.2 Derivation: the -6 dB threshold corresponds to a 25% increase in system) Tj T*
(56  noise temperature per ITU-R RA.769 Table 1.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(4. Protection Criteria) Tj T*
(60  4.1 The -6 dB I/N protection criterion for FSS earth stations is adopted.) Tj T*
(64  4.1 This is consistent with Radio Regulations and ITU-R Recommendations.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(5. Numerical Results) Tj T*
(70  5.1 Propagation model: ITU-R P.452 for transhorizon, free-space for LOS.) Tj T*
(74  5.3 Path loss calculations used the composite P.452 model [see Section 5.1].) Tj T*
(78  5.3 Table 5.1 shows minimum separation distances for each deployment scenario.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(6. Conclusions) Tj T*
(84  6.1 Spectrum sharing is feasible with: max EIRP +23 dBm/MHz; 50 km coordination) Tj T*
(88  zones around FSS sites; OOB emissions per ITU-R SM.1541.) Tj T*
(92  6.2 Administrations should coordinate with incumbent operators prior to licensing.) Tj T*
